  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A new electromyography (EMG)-driven neuromuscular electrical stimulation (NMES)-cycling
      system is introduced to stroke survivors for lower-limb rehabilitation. The system will
      generate NMES to targeted muscle according to the user's voluntary intention, represented by
      the EMG signal during cycling.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
